On receiving a record of a conviction of a person for a violation described in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Administration shall issue to the person a notice of suspension of the person's license that:
States that the person's license shall be suspended for 1 year;
States that the period of the first 45 days of the 1-year period of suspension is not subject to modification by the Administration;
States a restricted license may be issued for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension if:
The person maintains an ignition interlock system on a motor vehicle owned or operated by the person for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension;
The license is restricted to prohibit the person from driving a motor vehicle that is not equipped with an ignition interlock system;
The license is restricted to permit the person to drive only to and from work, school, an alcohol treatment program, or an ignition interlock system service facility, if the person was convicted of a violation of § 21-902(a) of this article more than once within a 5-year period; and
The license is restricted to permit the person to drive only to and from work, school, an alcohol treatment program, a drug treatment program, or an ignition interlock system service facility, if the person was convicted of:
Advises the person of the requirements under paragraph (7) of this subsection for a person who does not participate in the Ignition Interlock System Program in accordance with this paragraph during the 1-year period of suspension;
Advises the person of the right to request a hearing on a suspension under this paragraph; and
Advises the person of the right, instead of requesting a hearing on a suspension under this paragraph, to be subject to a 1-year period of suspension, with the period of the first 45 days of the suspension not subject to modification by the Administration, and for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension to be issued a restricted license under this paragraph if the following conditions are met:
The person's driver's license is not currently suspended, revoked, canceled, or refused;
The violation did not arise out of circumstances that involved a death of, or serious physical injury to, another person;
The person surrenders a valid Maryland driver's license or signs a statement certifying that the driver's license is no longer in the person's possession; and
The person elects in writing, within the same time limit for requesting a hearing, to meet the ignition interlock system requirements under this paragraph for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension.

The Administration may modify a suspension under paragraph (4) of this subsection to:
Impose a suspension of 45 days;
Order the person to maintain, for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension, an ignition interlock system on a motor vehicle owned or operated by the person; and
Impose a restriction on the person's license for the remainder of the 1-year period of suspension that prohibits the person from driving a motor vehicle that is not equipped with an ignition interlock system and permits the person to drive only to and from:
Work, school, an alcohol treatment program, or an ignition interlock system service facility, if the person was convicted of a violation of § 21-902(a) of this article more than once within a 5-year period;
